The paper deals with image classification using clustering and Bayesian networks, which are common techniques in computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG). The focus is on classifying images of faces, which falls under the subfield of facial recognition (cs.MM) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper involves the use of low-level features such as color and texture, which are relevant to information retrieval (cs.IR).
